Install a debian (.deb) package
	# dpkg -i <XYZ.deb>

List all installed packages
	# dpkg -l
	
Remove a package
	# dpkg -r <XYZ>
	
	# dpkg -p <XYZ> (including config files)
	
View the content of a package
	# dpkg -c <XYZ.deb>
	
Check a package is installed or not
	# dpkg -s <XYZ>
	
Check the location of installed packages
	# dpkg -L <XYZ>
	
Install all packages from a directory
	# dpkg -R --install <folder>/
	
Unpack the package but dont configure
	# dpkg --unpack <XYZ.deb>
	
Reconfigure a unpacked package
	# dpkg --configure <XYZ>
	
Replace available package information
	# dpkg --update-avail package_name
	
Erase existing available information of package
	# dpkg --clear-avail
	
Forget uninstalled and available packages
	# dpkg --forget-old-unavail
	
Display dpkg License
	# dpkg --license
	
Display dpkg version
	# dpkg --version
